main event: A bright round or oval-shaped object was sighted in San Francisco between March 24 and April 5, 1966.
interesting points: The object was described as extremely bright, initially appearing like a great star and later resembling a full moon., The sighting lasted approximately 20 to 30 seconds., The object changed appearance from a point source to a larger irregular-shaped light., No physical evidence or photographs were recorded., Witnesses reported it moving slowly at first before disappearing below the horizon.
sighted object: extremely bright round or oval-shaped object
witness description: an electrical engineer at the U.S. Naval Ordnance Test Station
